[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing error handling in testing**\n\nI’m considering how `getDeclaredPointcuts` handles exceptions. If it throws, I can test the exception message, but there’s a risk of it failing if the native reflection isn’t configured. I’m unsure if `AssertThrows` for `IllegalStateException` would work if there's no direct reflection configuration. It seems that on JVM, with the correct debug variables, `getDeclaredPointcuts` would succeed, but `assertThrows` might not, introducing some complexity in the testing process.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07c349ec691ba1690169f1a2df2d348194a2ee17a6161cc30d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8aLqagnWGeKlm78d9K3wSNbl55q05tyFh_a9vFF2Z_SbrKpGvW63eb0dTcXLkLZjWfu5DrDqcuN6KSwVf62lKKZJrOnOlM5OoFS1y86XE5TMAFcy5etkqMl83zpozq-8oy-I5QBpx-S7dZ878BQJnwddD7Q-jGprmpzlWUamVW8X_thv62JhPwY8rjS_TqhwYL-aHQRtbTEkJK8jR6mzyn2o6lVLEwco_qdnNI3SuDeQkD3YFWpQHQ9D_uuuJjQDt9BtJLW38SKBLQTpv4BvfcVlbN8rNFwSjwLVnI6sKW6hPA_PCXh-6ML30eAHvsjmAA6Tpx95oY7Tm7Yw3SVr87DI8hqpIioz7dNA52ekSI5BQMiKAWhNv3qBGxnxUv3MHw5nP_A8q3DDnb4CxswGX4TOdtukv994GYIWABCAq0Z2mswaXWzm5O1TOZHzQ-TL5mAXZIcgO__sq-4i2XIAELdqJV722N2TuDVA1zY2JojXnlSVkYCYxr0Hbf3Ru7iR5_ScrMawBYWCvG-PQzTz6dp6Sm5MKaEteIqMM6Uf3GOqzZZ_ews_RWJl92E9tGp6vMtN7o-bNt9oNKe8-RYKAogpeEuiOYWFESTiC_kzo9fr0DkUQJqy14vjdmQP7YCnpdSsdDJXjO_sTzWYnCjRLP0aE53GTAKq-X54bxwbK-mSpqqixPPKKfzb0qiAIOpqh3Sc-qp6W1O3BhzxZnevlc6T_S7Mokb5TMDAHXy5RWpHoqvDO5KiOl-MW0RelYfe9ax0sAiIKiKVwItLTsEeLF1t_rYgrCW9fdMyGNKyn_aVBxe0go7_bY8n5L9H48xJEJvga4GsX08fBA1SMrUcoA2hnT9sd6iGuH43V1fBeAM8YtzdYkvWSm59qWFhABuQgVoIY_jV8vMfFOrbQi6dEntt7pHck5ba9ZRt7OqFzay2W2YiDfo3JZWxPHIKtQm7lw36U_7wKz8rYA7HRJFDQCl5OqGSHSRUxBGQcj6Z4bTI1JXMcMha800Qn3yw9NX2Es7A73KZRw5Q__tVOjE98Q88xU6a5cbGIRHdMspRMNKrPCVKD_0WmIxWUQLjlM-kA5ab39vaQQd8eIp_NUKP6-r6Ns-AcoI-Zu6ZSMxYBkQ7RSXfUp9qwGxps92pz_sb1pP30VtP7uOtYTAMS-VADl5LHrGohy3AFj0BEznrnWix1pmRbIKYOIDUSgwy693SsvDKWuu6ooK